water 345g
NaOH 137g
oil 907g (750mL=708g)
essential oil: up to 28g

add lye to water (not the other way around!)
mix and let cool for 10+min (supposedly becomes transparent) while oil heats on high
turn oil to low and mix above. at some point add essential oils
wait several hours until it becomes harder and collapses over, add stuff (s.a. coarse salt / coffee / ...), mix again and wait
shape soaps and put them in containers (s.a. cardboard) and wait 24 hours to use

source: https://wellnessmama.com/23840/slow-cooker-soap-recipe/
